nts1.n: MUSIC TO EASE YOUR DISEASE W/ Jemima
ROLAS W/ ABE PEDROZA: TRISTES Y ROMÁNTICAS (R)
nts1.d: Abe Pedroza selects an hour of teark-jerking and romantic music from the Spanish speaking world – boleros, ballads, and moody instrumentals – “pairs well with a game of dominoes con los Tíos”.
Tropical rhythms, devotional boogie and soulful shenanigans with a heavy jazz undertone, Patrick Forge gathers it all up for your listening pleasure.

nts1.n: JAPANESE JAZZ WEEK: THREE BLIND MICE SPECIAL (R)
nts1.d:
Three Blind Mice is a jazz label set up by producer Takeshi Fujii in 1970. The label focused on Japanese jazz artists, and it's often called the Japanese Blue Note. It was renowned for the quality of its recordings (most of which were recorded by engineer Yoshihiko Kannari), and its incredible artwork. 
In this third episode of our Japanese Jazz Week series, we’ll hear many of the label’s artists, including Isao Suzki, Kosuke Mine, & Masaru Imada.
今回はジャズレーベル『スリー・ブラインド・マイス』特集です。『スリー・ブラインド・マイス』は、藤井武らによって、日本の新進気鋭の演奏者たちを世に出すことを目指して1970年6月に設立された日本のジャズ専門レーベルで、時には「日本のBlue Note」と形容されることも。スタジオエンジニアのYoshihiko Kannariによる高いレコーディング技術や、美しいアートワークによって注目されてきました。
第3回となる今回は、『スリー・ブラインド・マイス』の鈴木勲、峰厚介、今田勝他さまざまなのアーティストの曲をお届けします。Translated by Satoko Akune.
The Cleaners From Venus frontman presents an eclectic mix of pop music, comedy, and more.

nts1.n: TIME IS AWAY: The Fruit of this World is Falling
nts1.d:
Time Is Away and somewhere else every month on NTS. Each hour-long show uses music, alongside snippets of spoken word, to produce something that is part soundscape, part essay for the radio. 
From the host: "In Winter, the earth is like a body grown old. Now, before spring’s sprouting, we see everything as it will be at the end."
Get radiant with Ruby Savage's mixed bag of goodies.

Heavy vinyl records collector Dr. Kruger digs deep every other Sunday to bring soulful, funky and odd tunes from his crates straight to your home. Sometimes joined by a fellow crate digger/DJ of his choice, just tune in and let the doctor treat you.

Veteran NTS host Hampus brings you Doing Time: a genre-agnostic monthly trip through quality records from around the world’s past and present, featuring regular appearances from musical friends and family.

Chris Menist’s Paradise Bangkok label hits the NTS airwaves for a rundown of the best folk music from Africa, Indonesia and more. Reggae and Jazz rub shoulders with Gamalan as Menist uncovers classics; folk music without borders.
Basma shares songs and stories from passings through Khartoum and beyond.

nts1.n: A Month of Sundays w/ Bill Spencer
nts1.d: Bill Spencer shares weekend recordings from his living room studio in Detroit, Michigan, from where he brings a range of soulful jazz rock, and ambient sounds, spanning to electronica and psychedelic dub.

nts1.n: m00dtapes Special w/ Rod Coombes AKA My Dad
nts1.d:
Music Supervisor and DJ Dhamirah Coombes brings a monthly multi-genre curation of m00d-bending tracks intended for a deep listening experience.
From the host: _"This is a very special episode that I’ve been wanting to do for a long time. Curated with my father Rod Coombes – Drummer (Stealers Wheel / Strawbs), music savant, creative genius, gentle and warm soul, this is a collection of tracks that have shaped and bonded us as family and music lovers." _

nts1.n: THE GREAT AFRICAN DISCO W/ TEMI KOGBE - Afro Boogie

nts2.n: WEAPONISE YOUR SOUND W/ DIET CLINIC

subtle.d: Established in 2013, eatmybeat is a hybrid record label & club brand that was brought together by a group of friends with a passion for electronic music and building community. With diverse tastes, they support and champion the underground bass music scene through events and releases on the label. Refusing to be pigeonholed into a specific sound, they showcase everything from hip-hop, bass & breaks, through to techno, jungle, dubstep and grime. As long as it's tasty and full fat, you best believe eatmybeat are snacking on it.

Born and bred in Hackney, East London. SK’s influences include Rare Groove, Motown, Hip Hop, Soul, RnB, Reggae and Lovers Rock, he first started DJ’ing in 1992 on the Hardcore/Jungle scene under the name of DJ Slick making a number of appearances on the pirate radio scene and producing a number of underground white-label beats.
Born in Sunderland, based in London, Kitschko's productions and selections display a deep appreciation of UK club culture, and an affinity for late night, introspective sounds.

As a drummer since childhood, Chacho has always had an insatiable appetite for new and unique beats.
Combining his love of global percussion, dark grooves and deeper low end frequencies, 
his sets feature a blend of dubstep, grime, garage, breaks, hip hop and other flavours from around the world.

ixxi and Fei take you on a percussive journey with their show syncop8, moving from downtempo ambient to breaks, polyrhythms, and high energy beats, exploring every rhythmic and textural nuance in between.
Representing UK Bass Music Culture across a range of styles, sounds and tempos.

Rolling through varied tempo's and genres, Jimmy 2 Shoes brings dance floor orientated vibes and flows to wriggle your toes to. Expect eclectic selections and the freshest sounds from the UK underground.

As if kid is a professional Producer, DJ and Drummer from the west country (UK). Real name "Sid", He is versatile in producing hot records in various genres: Grime, UK Drill, Hip Hop, Jungle and more with an ever-growing number of global commercial placements and releases. He regularly collaborates with DJ Slimzee under alias E3 Breaks and with DJ Raggs under the alias Slamfire!

subtle.n: The Wheel Up Show w/ Tripta
subtle.d: Tripta is a Toronto based producer/DJ focusing on the darker sounds of Grime. Also blending elements of Drill, Dubstep and even Jungle all together for a unique sound you won't hear anywhere else. Signed to Slimzee's 'Slimzo's Recordings' and ‘Rotpot Records’.

Sound Arkitek is a Chicago hip-hop DJ with a love for all things drum & bass. 

With over 20 years experience playing house parties, raves, clubs and bars he has an encyclopedic knowledge of music but has always been a participant in jungle culture. In the early 2000s he was exposed to the genre primarily through Dieselboy and Danny The Wildchild mixes as well as the “Jungle Book” series of mixtapes. He became obsessed after hearing Bad Company’s “The Nine” and “Four Days,” as well as Pendulum’s “Vault.” 

As time went on, he got deeper into the scene, going to raves while buying records and posting on Drum & Bass Arena and DNBForum before turning 21 at which point he began going to Lava Lounge for Bass By The Pound’s “Seminar” series. The first legal drum & bass party he attended was Chase & Status at the aforementioned Lava Lounge, and he will never forget the energy when the duo played DJ Hazard’s “Killers Don’t Die” and it got a rewind. His love for the scene led to him playing drum & bass parties, opening for artists like Original Sin, Gridlok, and LTJ Bukem among others. 

His Subtle Radio show is an hour of the finest tunes in the scene at the moment. 

To keep up, follow @djsoundarkitek on Instagram!

Darcy is 23 year old DJ from Bristol who specialises in dubstep and grime. With a love for choppy techniques and old school grime cyphers, her sounds create a unique energy that reflect in her sets and mixes. 

New to the scene, she has played alongside 140 legends like Just Jane, White Peach Records, Riz la Teef and more. Working closely with underground labels like Partum Audio, as well as curating a montly show for her residency on Mondo Radio- Darcy continues to develop her style and make her name.

Hosted by Mirage, founder of Dubversified Culture, a community-led organization focusing on music, art, and events. subtle.d: Potent Funk records’ Matt Frost - Well known for his technical abilities and Sleazy bass music style, Frost covers all angles from UK alt Rap to the LA beat scene.

Get ready to embark on a captivating sonic journey of underground music with Charlie Kelly. Including new and timeless sounds from the depths of rap, drill, grime, and experimental genres from the vibrant streets of the UK and beyond. Charlie unearths the very best in music that pushes boundaries. Off the mic, Charlie is a Radio Producer and Social Media Executive with an eclectic music taste spanning across many different cultures, decades, and styles. Hailing from North London with a love for audio and pop culture, you can expect to hear tune after tune when you’re locked into Charlie Kelly on Subtle.
